agentBGPQueueIndex.description: Index value for this work queue.

agentBGPQueueLength.description: The number of items currently in the work queue.

agentBGPQueueDrops.name: agentBGPQueueDrops
agentBGPQueueDrops.description: The number of items dropped because the work queue was full.

agentBGPQueueLimit.name: agentBGPQueueLimit
agentBGPQueueLimit.description: The maximum number of items this queue can hold.

agentBGPOutNotifications.name: agentBGPOutNotifications
agentBGPOutNotifications.description: The total number of BGP NOTIFICATION messages transmitted since BGP counters were last cleared.

agentBGPInKeepalives.name: agentBGPInKeepalives

agentBGPOutKeepalives.name: agentBGPOutKeepalives

agentBGPInUpdatesMax.description: The maximum rate of BGP UPDATE messages received. The rate is given in packets per second.

agentBGPOutUpdatesMax.name: agentBGPOutUpdatesMax
agentBGPOutUpdatesMax.description: The maximum rate of BGP UPDATE messages transmitted. The rate is given in packets per second.

agentBGPDecProcTable.name: agentBGPDecProcTable
agentBGPDecProcTable.description: This table contains information about the twenty most recent executions of any of the three decision process phases. The most recent information is at the end of the table. This table is applicable to IPv4 address family only.

agentBGPDecProcEntry.name: agentBGPDecProcEntry
agentBGPDecProcEntry.description: Information about execution of a single decision process phase.

agentBGPDecProcIndex.name: agentBGPDecProcIndex
agentBGPDecProcIndex.description: Integer that uniquely identifies a decision process run. This value is incremented each time BGP runs one phase of the decision process.

agentBGPDecProcDeltaT.name: agentBGPDecProcDeltaT
agentBGPDecProcDeltaT.description: How long since this decision process ran. The time is given in seconds.

agentBGPDecProcPhase.name: agentBGPDecProcPhase
agentBGPDecProcPhase.description: Which of the three decision process phases was run.

agentBGPDecProcUpdateGroup.name: agentBGPDecProcUpdateGroup
agentBGPDecProcUpdateGroup.description: This variable is only valid when agentBGPDecProcPhase is 3. When the phase is 3, this variable identifies the outbound update group for which phase 3 was run. When the variable has a value of 65535 then it means that the corresponding agentBGPDecProcEntry does not belong to any outbound update group

agentBGPDecProcGenId.name: agentBGPDecProcGenId
agentBGPDecProcGenId.description: The global generation ID when the decision process ran.

agentBGPDecProcReason.name: agentBGPDecProcReason
agentBGPDecProcReason.description: Reason why the decision process was run.

agentBGPDecProcPeer.name: agentBGPDecProcPeer
agentBGPDecProcPeer.description: This variable is only valid when phase 1 is run for a single peer. In this case, this variable is the IP address of the peer for which phase 1 was run.

agentBGPDecProcDuration.name: agentBGPDecProcDuration
agentBGPDecProcDuration.description: How long the decision process ran. Milliseconds.

agentBGPDecProcAdds.name: agentBGPDecProcAdds
agentBGPDecProcAdds.description: Number of prefixes added during the decision process. For phase 1, this is the number of prefixes that pass inbound policy. For phase 2, this is the number of prefixes added to the BGP routing table. For phase 3, this is the number of prefixes added to the Adj-RIB-Out.

agentBGPDecProcMods.name: agentBGPDecProcMods
agentBGPDecProcMods.description: Number of prefixes modified during the decision process. For phase 1, this is the number of prefixes that pass inbound policy. For phase 2, this is the number of routes modified. For phase 3, this is the number of routes modified in the Adj-RIB-Out.

agentBGPDecProcDels.name: agentBGPDecProcDels
agentBGPDecProcDels.description: Number of prefixes deleted during the decision process. For phase 1, this is the number of prefixes that previously passed inbound policy but no longer pass. For phase 2, this is the number of prefixes removed from the BGP routing table. For phase 3, this is the number of prefixes removed from the Adj-RIB-Out.

agentBGPDecProcDeltaTIPv6.name: agentBGPDecProcDeltaTIPv6

agentBGPDecProcPhaseIPv6.name: agentBGPDecProcPhaseIPv6
agentBGPDecProcPhaseIPv6.description: Which of the three decision process phases was run.

agentBGPDecProcUpdateGroupIPv6.name: agentBGPDecProcUpdateGroupIPv6
agentBGPDecProcUpdateGroupIPv6.description: This variable is only valid when agentBGPDecProcPhase is 3. When the phase is 3, this variable identifies the outbound update group for which phase 3 was run. When the variable has a value of 65535 then it means that the corresponding agentBGPDecProcIPv6Entry does not belong to any outbound update group

agentBGPDecProcGenIdIPv6.name: agentBGPDecProcGenIdIPv6
agentBGPDecProcGenIdIPv6.description: The global generation ID when the decision process ran.

agentBGPDecProcReasonIPv6.name: agentBGPDecProcReasonIPv6

agentBGPDecProcDurationIPv6.description: How long the decision process ran. Milliseconds.

agentBGPDecProcAddsIPv6.name: agentBGPDecProcAddsIPv6
agentBGPDecProcAddsIPv6.description: Number of prefixes added during the decision process. For phase 1, this is the number of prefixes that pass inbound policy. For phase 2, this is the number of prefixes added to the BGP routing table. For phase 3, this is the number of prefixes added to the Adj-RIB-Out.

agentBGPDecProcModsIPv6.name: agentBGPDecProcModsIPv6
agentBGPDecProcModsIPv6.description: Number of prefixes modified during the decision process. For phase 1, this is the number of prefixes that pass inbound policy. For phase 2, this is the number of routes modified. For phase 3, this is the number of routes modified in the Adj-RIB-Out.

agentBGPDecProcDelsIPv6.name: agentBGPDecProcDelsIPv6

agentBGPPeerTable.name: agentBGPPeerTable
agentBGPPeerTable.description: BGP peer table. This table contains, one entry per BGP peer, information about connections with BGP peers.

agentBGPPeerEntry.name: agentBGPPeerEntry
agentBGPPeerEntry.description: Entry containing information about the connection with a BGP peer.

agentBGPPeerRemoteAddr.name: agentBGPPeerRemoteAddr
agentBGPPeerRemoteAddr.description: The remote IP address of this entry's BGP peer.

agentBGPPeerInOpens.name: agentBGPPeerInOpens
agentBGPPeerInOpens.description: The number of BGP OPEN messages received from this peer.

agentBGPPeerOutOpens.name: agentBGPPeerOutOpens
agentBGPPeerOutOpens.description: The number of BGP OPEN messages transmitted to this peer.

agentBGPPeerInUpdates.name: agentBGPPeerInUpdates
agentBGPPeerInUpdates.description: The number of BGP UPDATE messages received from this peer.

agentBGPPeerOutUpdates.name: agentBGPPeerOutUpdates
agentBGPPeerOutUpdates.description: The number of BGP UPDATE messages transmitted to this peer.

agentBGPPeerInNotifications.name: agentBGPPeerInNotifications
agentBGPPeerInNotifications.description: The number of BGP NOTIFICATION messages received from this peer.

agentBGPPeerOutNotifications.name: agentBGPPeerOutNotifications
agentBGPPeerOutNotifications.description: The number of BGP NOTIFICATION messages transmitted to this peer.

agentBGPPeerInKeepalives.name: agentBGPPeerInKeepalives
agentBGPPeerInKeepalives.description: The number of BGP KEEPALIVE messages received from this peer.

agentBGPPeerOutKeepalives.name: agentBGPPeerOutKeepalives
agentBGPPeerOutKeepalives.description: The number of BGP KEEPALIVE messages transmitted to this peer.

agentBGPPeerInRouteRefreshes.name: agentBGPPeerInRouteRefreshes
agentBGPPeerInRouteRefreshes.description: The number of BGP ROUTE REFRESH messages received from this peer.

agentBGPPeerOutRouteRefreshes.name: agentBGPPeerOutRouteRefreshes
agentBGPPeerOutRouteRefreshes.description: The number of BGP ROUTE REFRESH messages transmitted to this peer.

agentBGPPeerInTotalMessages.name: agentBGPPeerInTotalMessages
agentBGPPeerInTotalMessages.description: The total number of BGP messages of all types received from this peer.

agentBGPPeerOutTotalMessages.name: agentBGPPeerOutTotalMessages
agentBGPPeerOutTotalMessages.description: The total number of BGP messages of all types transmitted to this peer.

agentBGPPeerUpdateQueueLen.name: agentBGPPeerUpdateQueueLen
agentBGPPeerUpdateQueueLen.description: After receiving a BGP UPDATE message, BGP places each UPDATE on a per-neighbor queue before processing the UPDATE. This variable gives the current length of this peer's UPDATE queue, in bytes.

agentBGPPeerUpdateQueueHigh.name: agentBGPPeerUpdateQueueHigh
agentBGPPeerUpdateQueueHigh.description: The maximum length (or high water mark) of this peer.s UPDATE queue, in bytes.

agentBGPPeerUpdateQueueLimit.name: agentBGPPeerUpdateQueueLimit
agentBGPPeerUpdateQueueLimit.description: The maximum number of bytes of received UPDATE messages that may be queued for this peer at any given time.

agentBGPPeerUpdateQueueDrops.name: agentBGPPeerUpdateQueueDrops
agentBGPPeerUpdateQueueDrops.description: The number of UPDATE messages from this peer that could not be added to the UPDATE queue because the queue was full.

agentBGPPeerInPfxAdv.name: agentBGPPeerInPfxAdv
agentBGPPeerInPfxAdv.description: The number of IPv4 prefixes received from this peer.

agentBGPPeerOutPfxAdv.name: agentBGPPeerOutPfxAdv
agentBGPPeerOutPfxAdv.description: The number of IPv4 prefixes advertised to this peer.

agentBGPPeerInPfxWithdrawn.name: agentBGPPeerInPfxWithdrawn
agentBGPPeerInPfxWithdrawn.description: The number of IPv4 prefixes this peer has withdrawn.

agentBGPPeerOutPfxWithdrawn.name: agentBGPPeerOutPfxWithdrawn
agentBGPPeerOutPfxWithdrawn.description: The number of IPv4 prefixes this router has withdrawn in UPDATE messages to this peer.

agentBGPPeerInPfxCurrent.name: agentBGPPeerInPfxCurrent
agentBGPPeerInPfxCurrent.description: The number of IPv4 prefixes this peer is currently advertising to this router and that have passed inbound policy.

agentBGPPeerOutPfxCurrent.name: agentBGPPeerOutPfxCurrent
agentBGPPeerOutPfxCurrent.description: The number of IPv4 prefixes this router is currently advertising to this peer.

agentBGPPeerInPfxAccepted.name: agentBGPPeerInPfxAccepted
agentBGPPeerInPfxAccepted.description: The number of IPv4 prefixes received from this peer that may be considered to be included in the BGP route table. This includes all current prefixes whose path does not have an AS path loop and whose BGP NEXT HOP is resolved.

agentBGPPeerInPfxRejected.name: agentBGPPeerInPfxRejected
agentBGPPeerInPfxRejected.description: The number of IPv4 prefixes from this peer that did not pass inbound policy.

agentBGPPeerInMaxNlriPerUpdate.name: agentBGPPeerInMaxNlriPerUpdate
agentBGPPeerInMaxNlriPerUpdate.description: The maximum number of IPv4 prefixes in any single UPDATE message from this peer.

agentBGPPeerOutMaxNlriPerUpdate.name: agentBGPPeerOutMaxNlriPerUpdate
agentBGPPeerOutMaxNlriPerUpdate.description: The maximum number of IPv4 prefixes in any single UPDATE message sent to this peer.

agentBGPPeerInMinNlriPerUpdate.name: agentBGPPeerInMinNlriPerUpdate
agentBGPPeerInMinNlriPerUpdate.description: The minimum number of IPv4 prefixes in any single UPDATE message from this peer.

agentBGPPeerOutMinNlriPerUpdate.name: agentBGPPeerOutMinNlriPerUpdate
agentBGPPeerOutMinNlriPerUpdate.description: The minimum number of IPv4 prefixes in any single UPDATE message sent to this peer.

agentBGPPeerOutPfxWithdrawnIPv6.name: agentBGPPeerOutPfxWithdrawnIPv6
agentBGPPeerOutPfxWithdrawnIPv6.description: The number of IPv6 prefixes this router has withdrawn in UPDATE messages to this peer.

agentBGPPeerInPfxRejectedIPv6.description: The number of IPv6 prefixes from this peer that did not pass inbound policy.

agentBGPPeerInMaxNlriPerUpdateIPv6.name: agentBGPPeerInMaxNlriPerUpdateIPv6
agentBGPPeerInMaxNlriPerUpdateIPv6.description: The maximum number of IPv6 prefixes in any single UPDATE message from this peer.

agentBGPPeerOutMaxNlriPerUpdateIPv6.description: The maximum number of IPv6 prefixes in any single UPDATE message sent to this peer.
